<DocsLayout title="For Administrators" section="Timekeeping">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    This guide explains how administrators approve timecards and export them to QuickBooks
    for payroll and accounting. Once approved, timecards are locked from further edits.
  </p>
  <p>
    By eliminating double entry, this process reduces errors, ensures accurate data transfer,
    and streamlines payroll — saving both time and effort.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>From the left panel menu, click <strong>Timecards</strong> to view and edit</li>
    <li>Click the <strong>Actions</strong> button to perform different operations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Timecard Management</h2>
  <img src="/images/timekeeping/foradministrators_01.webp" alt="Edit Timecard" />

  <h3>Edit Timecard</h3>
  <p>Administrators can edit line items in the timecard before approval.</p>

  <h3>Approve Timecard</h3>
  <p>
    Clicking <strong>Approve</strong> locks the timecard from further edits once finalized.
  </p>

  <h3>Export to QuickBooks</h3>
  <p>
    Use the <strong>Send to QuickBooks</strong> option to export timecard data directly
    to QuickBooks Online for payroll processing.
  </p>

  <h2>QuickBooks Reporting</h2>
  <img src="/images/timekeeping/foradministrators_02.webp" alt="QuickBooks Report" />
  <p>
    View exported timecard data in QuickBooks under:
    <strong>Reports → Employees → Time Activities by Employee Detail</strong>
  </p>

  <h2>Approval Workflow</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Technician submits timecard for approval</li>
    <li>Administrator reviews and edits if necessary</li>
    <li>Administrator approves the timecard</li>
    <li>Export to QuickBooks for payroll</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Only <strong>Administrators</strong> can approve timecards and export to QuickBooks</li>
    <li>Administrators receive notifications when timecards are submitted for approval</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Ensure names match exactly</strong> in both QuickBooks and Field Promax for successful exports.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Approve timecards regularly</strong> to keep payroll on schedule.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Review time entries</strong> for discrepancies before approving.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
